{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"unfair-mindless-halcyon","description":"## Context\nEnforcement lives at the merge gate: a CI job verifies the required-environment certificate over the merged log and fails when a ticket that must carry one does not. This newly forbids landing an un-certified change in high-security projects.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A merge-gate CI job verifies the required-environment certificate over the merged log and fails on a missing/foreign cert (fixture test).\n- [ ] Every existing workflow trigger that should fire on the gate is classified INCLUDED/NO_FILTER (CI-trigger audit).\n- [ ] The new prohibition (cannot land un-certified) enumerates and classifies existing merge call-sites.","id":"4214-ac28-d19c-41b9","parent_id":"6d0d-7580-e18f-48c3","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"op-cert: merge-gate verification CI job over the merged log"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735894824752001,"uuid":"df90c019-b16a-4c86-ac6b-0d07bc1a45b6"}